implemented for that if the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isError"},{"text":" flag is risen.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Accessibility considerations","level":2,"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note also the component must be instanciated with a string parameter used as accessibility label."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It is a good pratice (at least) to define a label for a component without text for accessibility reasons. This label will be vocalized by ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Voice Over","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The vocalization tool will also use, after the label, a description of the component (if disabled, if error context), and a fake trait for checkbox."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Cases-forbidden-by-design","text":"Cases forbidden by design"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component."}]}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading","text":"Code samples"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have a selected checkbox","    @Published var isOn: Bool = true","","    \/\/ A simple checkbox, no error, not in read only mode","    OUDSCheckbox(isOn: $isOn, accessibilityLabel: \"The cake is a lie\")","","    \/\/ A simple checkbox, but is an error context","    OUDSCheckbox(isOn: $isOn, accessibilityLabel: \"The cake is a lie\"), isError: true)","","    \/\/ Never disable an error-related checkbox as it will crash","    \/\/ This is forbidden by design!","    OUDSCheckbox(isOn: $isOn, accessibilityLabel: \"The cake is a lie\"), isError: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error"],"syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Design documentation"},{"type":"